commentary: Amjad Javed to Rossouw, FOUR runs he hasn't scored too many runs of late, and looks to manufacture a pull. The ball is not short enough, and gets a top edge towards third man. Kamran Shahzad dives too early, and jams his knee straight into the ground. Not only has he conceded two extra runs, he has hurt his knee. That's awful. He tries to slide, but comes out an awkward angle and the knee gets stuck in the ground. He is back up and fielding

commentary: Amjad Javed to de Kock, OUT huge appeal for a catch at the wicket and a pretty aggressive review as Steve Davis turns the appeal down. A bit of an offcutter, a length ball outside off, de Kock pushes away from the body, gets a big edge, which is registered on the Snicko. Easy to overturn this. Yet another successful review against Davis. On this form, you'd hope he doesn't make it to the quarters. Everybody was convinced this was out, and the replays proved that. Sound, deviation, snicko, everything agrees

commentary: Mohammad Tauqir to Rossouw, OUT Tauqir has his reward. He is a lovely genuine offspinner. Puts his body into it, pivots beautifully, and lets the natural variation do the job for him. This one is slow in the air, on a length, just outside off, Rossouw is early into it, plays with hard hands, offers a simple return catch to Tauqir. Slightest bit of turn there. South Africa in a spot of bother here

commentary: Mohammad Tauqir to Miller, no run Haider has missed the run-out, or does he get it on the second grab? No he hasn't. For the second time this over, Miller wants a single after pushing one straight to short cover. De Villiers doesn't go this time, Miller slips while turning back, and is gone for all money. The throw, though, reaches Haider on a half-volley, and he fumbles the take, allowing Miller time to get back in. Actually this throw is a low full toss

commentary: Fahad Alhashmi to de Villiers, no run big shout for lbw, but this time they are not reviewing. Steve Davis has saved de Villiers, but this time they don't review it. What a big decision to not review it. Full inswinger, gentle pace, beats the inside edge, hits the front pad, then the back pad. That could have sounded like bat onto pad. No other reason to not give this. Oh UAE, why didn't you review this? It is plumb. Sunny Gavaskar on comms says, 'Davis loves to watch AB bat.' Oh hello, the Hawkeye stands firmly behind the umpire. Shows it is clipping leg. That projection beats me, though. In the end, a good decision to not review it, but I am sure this was given not-out because of two sounds

commentary: Philander to Amjad Ali, 2 leg byes he has shown him all the stumps by moving across, is hit on the pad, and goes for a leg-bye. The throw hits Beregner and wrong-foots Rossouw who is backing up. Ali, who doesn't know it has hit Berenger begins taking the overthrow. Berenger has no option but to go through. Rossouw is complaining even though Berenger is sort of apologising suggesting he couldn't do anything once his partner had come all the way up to the striker's end. Rossouw has no business showing righteousness. You are allowed to run off the body. Berenger has apologised too
